import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    yearly_disasters = data.groupby('Year').size()
    
    plt.plot(yearly_disasters.index, yearly_disasters.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the overall trend of natural disasters over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    total_deaths = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    total_deaths.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which type of natural disaster has caused the most deaths?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Deaths'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by natural disasters?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    yearly_data = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(yearly_data['Year'], yearly_data['Deaths'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the average number of deaths caused by natural disasters per year?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    disaster_counts = data['Entity'].value_counts()
    death_counts = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum()
    
    plt.scatter(disaster_counts, death_counts)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Number of Natural Disasters')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of natural disasters and the number of deaths?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
